@Size controls the size constraints on the collection, so it’s affecting the entire myothertypes map.  

maxOccurs relates to the number of occurrences of the element.
To control number of entries, create a custom validation mechanism with a custom getter method, then apply size constraint logic. 

java
import javax.validation.constraints.Size;
import java.util.Map;

public class YourClass {
    private Map&lt;MyothertypeEnum, Myothertype&gt; myothertypes;

    // Getter method with custom size validation logic
    @XmlElement
    public Map&lt;MyothertypeEnum, Myothertype&gt; getMyothertypes() {
        if (myothertypes.size() &gt; 2) {
            throw new IllegalStateException(&quot;myothertypes map size exceeds maximum allowed size of 2&quot;);
        }
        return myothertypes;
    }

    // Other methods and annotations for Myothertypes
}

