According to their logic in the current code base, we cannot have a retry configuration per connection factory:

       /**
         * Registers the ContainerFactory bean.
         */
        private SimpleRabbitListenerContainerFactory newContainerFactory(final ConnectionFactory connectionFactory) {
            final SimpleRabbitListenerContainerFactory containerFactory = new SimpleRabbitListenerContainerFactory();
            containerFactory.setConnectionFactory(connectionFactory);
            return containerFactory;
        }

So, they create a plain `SimpleRabbitListenerContainerFactory` based on the specific connection factory, but there is deep diving to the rest of `RabbitProperties` per connection factory.

See some official support for multi-rabbit in Spring AMQP: https://docs.spring.io/spring-amqp/docs/current/reference/html/#multi-rabbit

Since there is no clean and straightforward auto-configuration for this feature, I suggest you to look into a `setRetryTemplate()` of that `SimpleRabbitListenerContainerFactory` you have to configure per connection factory.

